: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u0650\u0633\u0652\u0648\u064e\u0631 \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u0645\u064e\u062e\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u0627\u0644 \u0642\u0627\u0644 \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631 \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062e\u064e\u0637\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650 \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064f \u0644\u064e\u0627 \u062d\u064e\u0638\u0651\u064e \u0641\u0650\u064a\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":26839,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/10\/29\/umar-most-important-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":13893,"position":1},"title":"Umar on Salat: Most important matter to me is prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 29, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Nafi\u2019 reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, wrote to his deputies, saying, \u201cVerily, the most important of your affairs to me is the prayer. Whoever maintains it and watches over it will maintain his religion. Whoever wastes it will be even more wasteful of other things.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":28901,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/09\/umar-dua-in-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":13893,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Dua: Umar ibn al-Khattab\u2019s supplication in prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 9, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"\u2018Abdah reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, would say these words aloud in prayer, \u201cGlory be to You, O Allah, with Your praises. Blessed is Your name, exalted is Your majesty. There is no God other than You.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 399 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37235,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/10\/27\/umar-dua-salat-ala-nabi\/","url_meta":{"origin":13893,"position":3},"title":"Umar on Dua: Supplication held back until the Prophet is blessed","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 27, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Sa\u2019id ibn al-Musayyib reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cVerily, the supplication is suspended between the heavens and the earth. Nothing ascends from it until you send blessings upon your Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 486 Grade: Sahih li ghayrihi\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25295,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/10\/22\/qiblah-salat-east-west\/","url_meta":{"origin":13893,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Qiblah: Prayer direction between two cardinal directions","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 22, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhatever is between east and west is the direction of prayer.\u201d Al-Tirmidhi said, \"It has been narrated from more than one of the companions of the Prophet, that what is between east and west is the direction of\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19909,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/10\/02\/anas-do-not-pray-to-graves\/","url_meta":{"origin":13893,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Graves: O Anas, do not pray towards the graves","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 2, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, saw me while I was praying near a grave and he raised his voice, saying, \u201cThe grave!\u201d I thought he said something else, so I looked toward the sky. Umar came and he said, \u201cIndeed, I said\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/13893","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.